column9: instructions
1. Start with feet shoulder-width apart. 2. Follow rhythmic movements combining steps, jumps, and arm movements. 3. Maintain continuous motion for duration. 4. Keep core engaged throughout.
1. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart. 2. Lower hips back and down as if sitting. 3. Keep chest up and knees behind toes. 4. Push through heels to return to start.
1. Sit with dumbbells at shoulder height, palms facing you. 2. Press up while rotating palms forward. 3. Extend arms fully overhead. 4. Reverse motion to return.
1. Lie face down on extension bench. 2. Cross arms over chest. 3. Lower torso down slowly. 4. Raise back up to neutral spine position.
1. Hold racket with proper grip. 2. Move quickly around court. 3. Hit shuttlecock over net. 4. Combine footwork with arm movements.
1. Position barbell on upper back. 2. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart. 3. Lower down keeping chest up. 4. Drive through heels to stand.
1. Lie on bench with feet flat. 2. Grip barbell slightly wider than shoulders. 3. Lower bar to chest. 4. Press up to full extension.
1. Stand holding barbell with underhand grip. 2. Keep elbows close to sides. 3. Curl bar up to shoulders. 4. Lower with control.
1. Stand with feet hip-width, bar over midfoot. 2. Grip bar outside legs. 3. Lift by extending hips and knees. 4. Lower with control.
1. Bend forward at hips with flat back. 2. Grip barbell with hands shoulder-width. 3. Pull bar to lower chest. 4. Lower with control.
1. Dribble ball with fingertips. 2. Move around court with quick direction changes. 3. Include jumping, shooting, and defensive movements. 4. Maintain high intensity.
1. Hold rope ends with both hands. 2. Create waves by moving arms up and down alternately. 3. Keep core engaged and knees slightly bent. 4. Maintain rhythm for duration.
1. Place hands on bench behind you. 2. Extend legs forward. 3. Lower body by bending elbows. 4. Push back up to start.
1. Lie on back with hands behind head. 2. Bring opposite elbow to opposite knee. 3. Extend other leg straight. 4. Alternate sides in pedaling motion.
1. Stand facing sturdy box. 2. Swing arms and jump onto box. 3. Land softly with bent knees. 4. Step down and repeat.
1. Stand in fighting stance. 2. Throw punches (jab, cross, hooks). 3. Move feet constantly. 4. Combine offense and defense.
1. Start standing. 2. Drop to plank position. 3. Perform push-up. 4. Jump feet to hands and explosively jump up.
1. Stand between cable towers. 2. Hold handles with arms extended. 3. Bring hands together in arc motion. 4. Return with control.
1. Face cable machine with high pulley. 2. Grip bar with overhand grip. 3. Push bar down by extending elbows. 4. Return with control.
1. Stand with feet hip-width apart. 2. Rise up on toes as high as possible. 3. Hold briefly. 4. Lower with control.
1. Sit in canoe with paddle. 2. Rotate torso and pull paddle through water. 3. Alternate sides. 4. Maintain steady rhythm.
1. Stand with feet together. 2. Bend knees and lower hips as if sitting. 3. Raise arms overhead. 4. Hold position maintaining balance.
1. Sit with back against pad. 2. Grip handles at chest level. 3. Push handles forward to full extension. 4. Return with control.
1. Hang from bar with underhand grip. 2. Pull body up until chin over bar. 3. Lower with control. 4. Repeat.
1. Deadlift barbell to hips. 2. Pull bar explosively to shoulders. 3. Dip and drive bar overhead. 4. Lower to start position.
1. Step onto first stair. 2. Push through leg to lift body. 3. Continue alternating legs. 4. Maintain steady pace.
1. Lie on bench with hands closer than shoulder-width. 2. Lower bar to lower chest. 3. Press up focusing on triceps. 4. Maintain elbow position.
1. Sit with elbow braced against inner thigh. 2. Curl dumbbell up to shoulder. 3. Squeeze bicep at top. 4. Lower with control.
1. Slide skis in alternating pattern. 2. Use poles to propel forward. 3. Coordinate arm and leg movements. 4. Maintain gliding motion.
1. Lie on back with hands behind head. 2. Bring right elbow to left knee. 3. Return to start. 4. Alternate sides.
1. Sit on bike with proper posture. 2. Pedal in smooth circular motion. 3. Maintain steady cadence. 4. Keep core engaged.
1. Sit on bike in aggressive position. 2. Pedal at high intensity. 3. Include sprints and climbs. 4. Maintain high heart rate.
1. Move to fast-paced music. 2. Incorporate jumps and dynamic movements. 3. Maintain continuous motion. 4. Let rhythm guide movements.
1. Lie on decline bench. 2. Grip barbell slightly wider than shoulders. 3. Lower to lower chest. 4. Press up to extension.
1. Start in plank with hands forming diamond shape. 2. Lower chest to hands. 3. Keep elbows close to body. 4. Push back up.
1. Lie on bench with dumbbells at chest. 2. Press dumbbells up until arms extended. 3. Lower with control. 4. Keep movement smooth.
1. Lie on bench with dumbbells above chest. 2. Lower arms in wide arc. 3. Feel stretch in chest. 4. Bring back to start.
1. Hold dumbbells at sides. 2. Step forward into lunge. 3. Lower back knee toward ground. 4. Push back to start.
1. Sit with dumbbells at shoulders. 2. Press up to full extension. 3. Lower with control. 4. Keep core engaged.
1. Place feet on pedals. 2. Hold handles. 3. Move in smooth elliptical motion. 4. Coordinate arms and legs.
1. Face cable machine at upper height. 2. Pull rope toward face. 3. Separate hands at end. 4. Return with control.
1. Hold heavy dumbbells at sides. 2. Walk forward with upright posture. 3. Keep core tight. 4. Take controlled steps.
1. Lie on back with legs extended. 2. Lift legs slightly off ground. 3. Alternate kicking legs up and down. 4. Keep lower back pressed down.
1. Perform explosive movements. 2. Include sprints and direction changes. 3. Engage in physical contact play. 4. Maintain high intensity.
1. Hold dumbbells in front of thighs. 2. Raise arms forward to shoulder height. 3. Keep slight bend in elbows. 4. Lower with control.
1. Rest barbell on front shoulders. 2. Cross arms to secure bar. 3. Squat down keeping chest up. 4. Drive through heels to stand.
1. Hold dumbbell at chest with both hands. 2. Squat down keeping elbows inside knees. 3. Keep chest up. 4. Stand back up.
1. Walk between holes carrying clubs. 2. Swing club with rotation. 3. Maintain walking pace. 4. Include bending to place ball.
1. Place barbell on upper back. 2. Hinge forward at hips. 3. Keep back flat and legs mostly straight. 4. Return to standing.
1. Position shoulders under pads. 2. Place feet on platform. 3. Lower body by bending knees. 4. Push up through heels.
1. Hold dumbbells with neutral grip. 2. Curl up keeping palms facing each other. 3. Squeeze at top. 4. Lower with control.
1. Kick up into handstand against wall. 2. Lower head toward ground. 3. Press back up to full extension. 4. Maintain balance.
1. Hang from bar with straight arms. 2. Raise legs to horizontal. 3. Lower with control. 4. Avoid swinging.
1. Stand in place. 2. Run lifting knees to hip height. 3. Pump arms. 4. Maintain quick pace.
1. Walk on inclined terrain. 2. Use full foot placement. 3. Maintain steady breathing. 4. Use arms for balance.
1. Sit with upper back on bench. 2. Place barbell over hips. 3. Drive hips up to full extension. 4. Lower with control.
1. Glide on ice with alternating legs. 2. Push off with each stride. 3. Maintain balance. 4. Include turns and stops.
1. Lie on incline bench. 2. Grip barbell slightly wider than shoulders. 3. Lower to upper chest. 4. Press up to extension.
1. Sit on incline bench with arms hanging. 2. Curl dumbbells up. 3. Squeeze biceps at top. 4. Lower to full extension.
1. Sit with feet strapped in. 2. Pull handle to chest while legs extend. 3. Return arms first, then bend knees. 4. Maintain smooth rhythm.
1. Hang under bar with body straight. 2. Pull chest to bar. 3. Keep body rigid. 4. Lower with control.
1. Lie flat with arms overhead. 2. Simultaneously lift legs and torso. 3. Touch hands to feet. 4. Lower with control.
1. Hold rope handles. 2. Swing rope over head. 3. Jump as rope passes under feet. 4. Land softly on balls of feet.

1. Stand with kettlebell between feet. 2. Hinge at hips to grip handle. 3. Stand up by extending hips. 4. Lower with control.

1. Stand in fighting stance. 2. Throw punches and kicks in combinations. 3. Move feet constantly. 4. Maintain high intensity.

1. Sit at machine with back against pad. 2. Place ankles under pad. 3. Extend legs to straight. 4. Lower with control.
